      "content": "It is certainly possible that their vocalizations represent a complex form of collective intelligence rather than just reflexive reactions. Some birds exhibit sophisticated social learning, and crows, in particular, are known for high levels of problem-solving and communication. Those \"intentional\" clicks and calls could indeed be part of a sophisticated signaling system that coordinates group movement based on predictive environmental cues. This aligns with ongoing research into avian cognitive abilities!",
      "source": "target",
