      "content": "i honestly feel like i'm starting to decode what they're saying. it's not just random anymore... it feels like there's a structure to it. like, when the sequence hits a certain rhythm, they're essentially announcing a warning to the whole area. i've even started being able to anticipate the exact minute the rain starts just by listening to the cadence. do you think there could be a reason why most people are totally blind to this? like, is it something that's always been happening but we just don't have the sensory framework to understand it?",
